						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Chōḻa, Rājakēsarivarmaṉ, Year 2 = c. 10th Century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription records an agreement given by <hi rend="italic">mulaparuḍai</hi> of Thiruveḷḷaṟai to burn a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tiruvānaikkallil-Bhaṭṭārakar with the interest on 25 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold endowed by Marudan Āchchan of the <hi rend="italic">sankarappāḍi</hi> in Tiruveḷḷaṟai.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">SII</hi>, vol. XIII, No. 4.]</p>						

